narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: I learned foundational mathematics for future math, economics, and computer science courses. I also learned more real-world applications of calculus and linear algebra.
most of linear algebra and some multivariable calculus knowledge

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: As a summer course, this class is very intensive and quick-paced. We learned 3 new topics per class, and it took a lot of time outside of class to make sure I had a real understanding of the content. However, the class size was really small so this allowed for a lot of peer-collaboration that proved very helpful.
materials were taught in a good order
Useful material, but very fast paced during summer and many concepts were left unexplained.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: I would recommend this class to any student that wants a good foundation in calculus before taking math 120. I feel prepared to further my multivariable calculus skills.

I would not recommend this course unless you have to take it, it was horribly designed. Quizzes at the beginning of each class that were meant to facilitate learning created an extremely stressful class environment, professor ning told us that they were meant to be difficult and not necessarily for us to finish it within the given time, but it was still worth 20% of our final grade.
No, take it during the regular year, not during summer.
